.TH EXAMPLE\-SENDER\-CPP 1 "May 2026" "mu2e\-daq\-alert 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
example\-sender\-cpp \- send a Mu2e DAQ alert using the C++ library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B example\-sender\-cpp
[\fB\-s\fR \fIID\fR]
[\fB\-m\fR \fITEXT\fR]
[\fB\-i\fR \fIADDRESS\fR]
[\fB\-p\fR \fINUM\fR]
[\fB\-h\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B example\-sender\-cpp
constructs a JSON alert payload and broadcasts it as a single UDP datagram.
It is a minimal demonstration of the
.B libdaq_alert_cpp
C++ library interface, specifically the
.B mu2e::daq::AlertSender
class.
.PP
The payload format is:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
{"system_id":"...","timestamp":"<ISO\-8601>","message":"..."}
.fi
.RE
.PP
The timestamp is generated automatically at the time of the call.
Send failures are reported as exceptions of type
.BR mu2e::daq::AlertError .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-system\-id " " \fIID\fR
Identifier of the sending system.
.br
Default: \fBDAQ\-NODE\-01\fR
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-message " " \fITEXT\fR
Human\-readable alert message.
.br
Default: \fBTest alert from example\-sender\-cpp\fR
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ip " " \fIADDRESS\fR
UDP broadcast destination address.
.br
Default: \fB255.255.255.255\fR
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fINUM\fR
UDP destination port (1\(en65535).
.br
Default: \fB37020\fR
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Send an alert with default parameters:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
example\-sender\-cpp
.fi
.RE
.PP
Send an alert to a specific subnet with a custom system ID and message:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
example\-sender\-cpp \-\-system\-id DAQ\-NODE\-03 \e
    \-\-message "Readout buffer overflow" \e
    \-\-ip 192.168.1.255
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Alert sent successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid argument or send failure.
.SH BUILDING
Build and install from the
.I libs/
directory of the repository:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
cmake \-B build \-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=./install
cmake \-\-build build
cmake \-\-install build
.fi
.RE
.PP
The installed binary is placed in
.IR <prefix>/bin/example\-sender\-cpp .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR example\-sender\-c (1),
.BR example\-sender\-py (1)
